input: Look for the UUIDs of bank accounts that have more than five entries and are associated with contracts that have a planned cancellation date set in the future.

output.sql: SELECT T1.UUID FROM BankAccount AS T1 JOIN BankAccountEntries AS T2 ON T1.UUID = T2.BankAccountUUID GROUP BY T1.UUID HAVING COUNT(T2.UUID) > 5 AND T1.PlannedCancellationDate > CURRENT_DATE;
